</mei>

<!--
VOICING PLAN:
- Throughout: LH carries open-position D-major voicings (D2 A2 D3 F#3 standard).
  For ii, iii, vi (minor chords), LH uses root-position minor with full 4-note spread.
  RH stays light with 2-note intervals (3rds and 5ths) except final bar (3 notes).
- Bar 3: Bm->F#m->A descent uses voice leading thirds in RH, open 5ths in LH.
- Bar 4: The Bm7 gets a 7th chord voicing (B D F# A) in LH for richness.
- Bar 6: "E major" annotation is non-diatonic in D; substituted Em (ii) diatonically.

VOICE LEADING HIGHLIGHTS:
- Bars 3-4: LH descends Bm→F#m→A→Em→Bm7 smoothly, each chord a step away from the last.
- Bar 7: RH descends C#→B→A (chromatic third motion) mirroring the melody descent.
- Bar 8: Both hands converge in contrary motion: RH descends G→F#→D (3rd), LH stays on D.

TEXTURE ARC:
- Bars 1-4 (first phrase): 2-note RH, 3-4-note LH. Sparse, open.
- Bars 5-6 (second phrase): Same but RH adds occasional 2-beat sustains.
- Bars 7-8 (cadence): RH expands to 3 notes at final D; LH holds full 4-note root position.
  Classical authentic V→I approach at bar 8.
-->
